g.text: Trash Container: This trash container is locked. The sliding lid has a padlock that says "Whirling-in-Rags."
You: "How do we get the lock open?"
You: Why am I looking at you, trash container? You're just a trash container.
You: Force time -- jam the tool under the lid and pull!
You: Open the padlock with the key.
Trash Container: The dumpster is goading you. It thinks you're weak.
Kim Kitsuragi: "The belt is missing. That's it. Do you see anything else in there? I have another bag here..."
Trash Container: Something slimy catches your eye...
Cuno: "Cuno can hear you, cop -- and Cuno don't know shit about the rags, okay? You don't have to come asking about them again like some bitch."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Information from that *source* has truly been invaluable to the investigation. I cannot wait to hear more."
Jump to: [Tutorial Agent: "Some items, such as the ledger you..."]
Tutorial Agent: Some items, such as the ledger you found, are interactable. Go to your INVENTORY and select the INTERACT tab to read your paperwork.

Kim Kitsuragi: "Do-eth thou also thorough inventories?" He points to the ruined notes. "You should take stock of your notes, make sure it's all there. Official notes contain informants' names. If some of it has fallen into the hands of the RCM's adversaries, bloodletting may well ensue."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I see, yes. You're what we call a *bad ass*, aren't you?" He makes little quotation marks around the words, indicating he is unsure of its actual badassery.
Rhetoric: Wow, went off script there, getting your ass handed to you. You shouldn't go picking fights if your rhetorical faculties haven't suggested it.
Kim Kitsuragi: With effort, he looks at you.
Empathy: Whatever he may feel in this moment is locked away deep inside him.
Trash Container: *Just* a trash container? There is no such thing.
Interfacing: Your fingers start to itch just looking at that padlock...
You: "I'm so disappointed right now. I thought there was a Remote Viewers Division."
Kim Kitsuragi: "None. Because they don't exist."
Physical Instrument: Prybar, prybar, your palms yearn it's cold touch. To grasp it once more, as you've done so many times...
Trash Container: This is where you belong...
Kim Kitsuragi: Soggy cartons and rags look back at him. "Oh yes -- and it would also be appropriate to start taking notes on the case. It's what cops do."
You: I'm not going to do anything.
Logic: Oh, yes you are. It's *fundamental* to proper police procedure to start keeping notes on the case at hand. Open your official investigation.
Logic: Exactly. Open your official investigation.
Jump to: [Trash Container: "You pick out a broken mug, with an..."]
Trash Container: You pick out a broken mug, with an oddly racist depiction of *the yellow man* frolicking in saffron.
Trash Container: Unsatisfying. Hurtful. You hear a ringing sound, but not quite hollow. The can seems to be full...
Half Light: *Full* of itself. Content, happy you failed. This snickering trash container is having a grand old time.
Trash Container: With a well-oiled crack the lock pops open. It should now be possible to simply raise the lid...
Inland Empire: Don't! Maybe you shouldn't...
Trash Container: And is that a Cordon Electrics pre amp with Elektra f2 tubes? It is! That catches quite a price, we're talking 12,000 easy. Unless you're into hi-fi yourself?
Kim Kitsuragi: "Mhm..." The lieutenant briefly glances at the mug, then returns his sight to the trash.
Trash Container: A blue piece of plastic sticks out from the apple peels. It's *shiny*. Looks like the corner of something...
Cunoesse: "The fuck's he on about -- *kid*?!" the one behind the fence yells. "You hear that, Cuno? He thinks you're an infant or some shit."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Did he? I must have drifted away... somewhere between the copious mentions of pigs and homo-sexuality."
Trash Container: Soggy carton and some kind of food sludge welcome you back, uninvitingly. Smells like the wrong choice.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Officer," the lieutenant adds, "This is sensitive information. You need to take this seriously."
You: "Yes, I *feel* like there's something in there."
Physical Instrument: Prybar, crowbar, leverage displacement tool of the gods. Your hands have held its paint-flaked metal one hundred thousand times.
Physical Instrument: *Still* not force time. You're just not getting there... the prybar is primed, but you lack the ability.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Officer..." the lieutenant says. "Now that you have your ledger back, it would not hurt to start taking notes on the case. Officially."
"You said you didn't want to talk about the ledger, however... now that you have it back, it would not hurt to start taking notes on the case. Officially."
Logic: Now that your ledger is back in your possession, it feels like you should do something... *important*.
You: What am I supposed to do?
Logic: You have to start taking proper notes on the case. Open your official investigation.
Perception (Sight): The rest of the rags are just kitchen-variety waste. Just garbage.
Perception (Sight): The rest of the rags are just kitchen-variety waste. A yellow old mug that catches your eye. But other than that...
Trash Container: Variable["yard.trash_kim_turned_from_digging"] == true and Variable["yard.trash_interfacing_deluxe_content"] == false and Variable["yard.trash_mug"] == false
Variable["yard.trash_kim_turned_from_digging"] == true and Variable["yard.trash_interfacing_deluxe_content"] == false and Variable["yard.trash_mug"] == false
!(Variable["yard.trash_kim_turned_from_digging"] == true and Variable["yard.trash_interfacing_deluxe_content"] == false and Variable["yard.trash_mug"] == false)
Kim Kitsuragi: "The quality of metal is not the problem. From what I see, it's sturdy enough."
Cuno: "Quit pushin' the blame on the metal piggo. Metal's fine. It's your arm that's shit."
Kim Kitsuragi: "The strange thing is -- we don't have to." He smiles. "We have the *key* remember. The manager gave you the key."
Trash Container: The smell of rotten food rises to greet you. You see soggy cartons, dirty rags, and organic waste.
You: Time for bed again. Crawl inside for real...
You: The mug, I'm getting that mug too.
You: Time for bed. Crawl inside...
Time for bed, Hobocop. Crawl inside...
You: Look under the boxes of carton.
You: Dig in Hobocop-style -- for extra content.
You: "The kid said he didn't know anything about the clothes."
Trash Container: The garbage stinks in front of you, overflowing with soggy cartons, dirty rags, and organic waste.
You: No! Not like this! (Crawl out of the trash.)
Trash Container: You crawl out of the trash container. The lid clangs shut. The fresh air rushes into your lungs, but does not clear them of the garbage stink.
You: "Then we should open it immediately!"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Mhm." He leans in to inspect the lock.
Logic: He might also have information -- this is better than the prybar idea.
Inland Empire: There's something in there. Not necessarily connected to the case -- but still...
Empathy: He's enjoying your little failure. He finds it amusing, he's revelling in the sweaty rage on your face.

Cuno: "No you weren't. If you were you'd stick that shitto..." He makes a move with his hands. "In that staple or some shit. That little ring that has the lock in it. Then twist that shit, it's the weak spot."
Cunoesse: "What are you his fuckin' sidekick now, Cun'? Don't listen to him pig, you were good."
Kim Kitsuragi: "We're just in time." The lieutenant peers in. "This hasn't been emptied for over a week."
Kim Kitsuragi: "That's one thing off the list..." The lieutenant sounds relieved. "I think we got it all."
Kim Kitsuragi: "We should return later, officer. I don't think we were thorough enough. There may be more in there."
Trash Container: Only in its social sensibility.

Kim Kitsuragi: "Alright. We should go to Garte again and ask if he knows who put the clothes in the trash. It could be as simple as someone from the hostel cleaning the yard, or *that* one..." He nods toward the red-haired boy behind him. "I'd advise *against* confronting that force."
Jump to: [Trash Container: "The smell of rotten food rises to g..."]
You: "I don't know, man. Sounds like an order. I don't take those."
Trash Container: The smell of rotten food rises up at you as you climb inside the trash container.
Kim Kitsuragi: "There isn't -- but we should still access this container."
Kim Kitsuragi: "We should still access this container. There may be evidence in there."
Trash Container: The lock says Whirling-in-Rags. Maybe the proprietor has the key? Who knows what secrets wait inside...
Trash Container: The lock says Whirling-in-Rags. Maybe the proprietor has the key? Who knows what secrets wait inside...
You: "But I wanted to use the prybar... I feel like I'm losing out on something not using the prybar."
Kim Kitsuragi: "You are. The prybar is quite satisfying and handy." He nods, without the slightest hint of irony. "But you are just not good enough at prying. We should get the keys."
Cuno: "Yeah, I know but what were you trying to do pig?"
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant nods, then looks back into the trash container.

Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't know either..." He points to the ruined notes. "You should take stock of your notes, make sure it's all there. Official notes contain informants' names. If some have fallen into the hands of the RCM's adversaries, bloodletting may well ensue."
Cunoesse: "The fuck's he on about -- *kids*?!" The one behind the fence yells. "You hear that, Cuno? He thinks you're an infant or something."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Tell me, *see-eth* your bad ass more in there or are we done here?" The lieutenant peers into the trash.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Tell me, does your bad ass see more in there or are we done here?" The lieutenant peers into the trash.
You: Elbows out, there's nothing more here.
You: "It's just a hunch. Maybe someone threw something in there?"
You: "It's extrasensory perception. Whatever is in there holds a special *significance*."
Kim Kitsuragi: "All the detectives from all the Precincts who experience extrasensory perception go to the Remote Viewers Division. Their work is invaluable to the force."
Drama: It's remarkable how he can keep a straight face. Take note -- the lieutenant is well versed in dead-panning. Many of the things he says could be meant in jest.
Trash Container: A box falls into pieces in your hands: Batiste *Soleil* cereal. There are plastic pasta packages below, and *Turbo* noodles. Nothing of note, however.
Kim Kitsuragi: "We could try using a prybar -- the one you took from my motor carriage. Or..."
Trash Container: The trash container stands in the spring snow.
You: "Damn, this reminds me: I got side- tracked asking Cuno about the rags... The damned FALN pants got in the way. We should ask again, Kim."
You: *Mine*? What is it doing in trash?
You: This makes a lot of sense.
Trash Container: As the legs of the slime-covered jeans begin to unspool from the garbage, a rank corpse smell fills the air.
Kim Kitsuragi: His gaze is focused on something nebulous in the far distance. On nothing in particular.
Kim Kitsuragi: He is as silent as the night.
Kim Kitsuragi: "No, because they don't exist."
Physical Instrument: You stick the prybar into the fissure beneath the lid and push down. It doesn't take much force -- with a satisfying *crack,* the metal gives way. You can open the lid now.
Trash Container: The container sounds a muffled gong.
Interfacing: 'Maybe you shouldn't...' Of course you should! This is your time to shine, Hobocop! Dive into that dumpster for extra content!
You: Didn't I just have a premonition that *there's something in there*?
Trash Container: It's a giant rifle and it's very expensive. Not as expensive as that fat string of pearls snaking among the rotten banana peels however...
You: Where?! I can't see it.
Trash Container: Never mind, look at that fat string of Archipelagoan pearls snaking amidst the banana peels!
Trash Container: Among the threadbare kitchen towels, something catches your eye -- a pair of denim trousers?

Kim Kitsuragi: "This is a military type over-garment. No label or serial number -- this is the kind of rib-knit shirt that's worn over light armour to conceal it in an urban scenario..." He nods to himself. "Anything more?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Officer, is that your... paperwork?"

Kim Kitsuragi: "It is, look..." He points to the clipboard. "The plastic has the RCM street grid on it. You've even got an autopsy form in there..." A miserable looking slip of paper sticks to the board.
Kim Kitsuragi: "If you don't mind me asking -- how did this get in the trash?"
"If you don't mind my asking, how could you have let your paperwork end up in the trash?"
Interfacing: It does? Maybe it does. It *might* have been thrown out by your hand. Feels like that anyway -- like *stuffed* it somewhere. Not in this trash though. How it got here you haven't a clue.
You: "It must have been cramping my style."
You: "It has a foreboding quality to it. Maybe I *needed* to lose it, for the Great Bloodletting to begin?"
You: "I think I didn't want to be a cop anymore, so I threw it away."
"I think I didn't want to be a cop anymore. That's why I tried to flush my cop life down the toilet."
You: "Someone from the Whirling threw it in the trash? I don't know. I'm boring."
You: "I'd rather not to talk about it right now."
Authority: Be untroubled. If anything, this small moment has made him respect you more.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Drop them in here, officer." The lieutenant produces a black plastic bag marked *evidence* from his pocket.
You: "By *early stages* you mean these were taken from him no more than two days after his death?"
You: "What kind of extra-natural abilities do they possess?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "We *might* want to ask for a key from the manager of the Whirling-in-Rags. He probably has one. And he also has *information*."
Physical Instrument: Ask *the manager*? Bullshit! Go straight for the prybar and pry this baby wide open!
Inland Empire: Beware. They're very *painful* secrets.
Physical Instrument: Force time isn't happening. You've jammed the prybar under the lid but it just isn't bending.
Half Light: WHAT IS THIS? Your triceps ache for the metal to bend, but it resists... this calls for a potent curse to help break it's resistance. Utter the POWER WORDS!
Cunoesse: "No he don't! He fuckin' lost it! The ape's lost the key too."
You: "You think someone from the Whirling might have been... involved maybe?"
You: "Yeah, we need to ask the kids who put them here."
You: What I should do is get back to that garbage. (Decline.)
Trash Container: Good choice. Soggy carton and some kind of food sludge welcome you back, invitingly.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Understood." He nods, reverting his attention to the container, still stinking in front of you.
You: "Sorry it had to be this way."
Kim Kitsuragi: He nods. Absent-mindedly, he reaches for a cigarette; no sooner has it left his pocket than he catches himself.
Kim Kitsuragi: He puts the cigarette back, and says: "Me too."
Trash Container: This is where you belong...
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant greets you with a small nod, as if you'd just taken a momentary pause to tie a shoelace.
Trash Container: The container remains as inviting as a coffin. It is ready whenever you are.
Tutorial Agent: You've acquired an interactable item. Investigate this item further by going to the INTERACT tab in your INVENTORY.
You: I should get you open, trash container.
Trash Container: The body is downwind from here. Maybe you prefer the smell of garbage to the smell of death?
Jump to: [Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant leans in to inspect..."]
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant leans in to inspect the lock.
You: It's not a *pry*bar, it's a crowbar.
Trash Container: No you won't, because none of those things are real. They're not actually in there. All you see is food waste and crisp wrappings.
Jump to: [Trash Container: "The garbage stinks in front of you,..."]

Esprit de Corps: This feels like something you should return to with Lieutenant Kitsuragi present. Also, it makes you feel like an idiot for not having an evidence bag on you -- what will you do with a dead man's trousers?
Kim Kitsuragi: "It would also not hurt to start taking notes on the case. Anyway, where were we..." The lieutenant peers into the trash container where soggy cartons and rags stink uninvitingly.
Trash Container: There's nothing more of interest in this sludge of peels and meat by-product. Try the carton or those stinking rags.
Trash Container: It's just organic waste, cold and slimy on your hands. Apple and potato peels mostly, unidentified sludge, and the occasional chicken bone thrown in for good measure. But hey...
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant averts his eyes as you crawl into the trash container.

Kim Kitsuragi: Darkness engulfs you. The stink of rot nearly knocks you out. For a minute you can smell cigarette smoke wafting in from outside -- then it is gone, and you hear footsteps walking away.
Trash Container: Well it is a *container*. Maybe you're prioritizing it?
Kim Kitsuragi: "Interesting." The lieutenant looks at the mug. "Reminds me of the mug collection we saw in our weasel's apartment. Maybe he or she has been dumping their garbage here?"
Logic: An interesting little clue. Let's see where this goes. Clues have a way of magically connecting to other clues -- down the road...
Reaction Speed: Yes! The one in the apartment you broke into. Interesting little clue. Surely this will yield something -- down the road...
Cuno: "Cuno's gotta say, man, that was unimpressive. The fuck were you trying to do?"
Interfacing: Yeah! Crack it open Hobocop -- this is your time to shine. Dive into that dumpster for extra content!
You: A cruel jest... there must be *something*...
Trash Container: All you see is a broken mug with a racist depiction of *the yellow man* frolicking in saffron.
You: I knew it. (Withdraw from the dumpster's cavernous depths.)

Trash Container: Something larger -- a clipboard! A blue plastic clipboard with moist papers hanging from it. They look badly damaged, but you can still make out forms and notes. Written in a *man's* handwriting...
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes it is, look." He points to it. "This plastic has the RCM street grid on it. You've even got an autopsy form..." A miserable looking slip of paper sticks to the board.
Interfacing: You don't know. It *might* have been by your hand, though. Feels like that. Feels like you might have stuffed it somewhere. Not in this trash though. How it got here you don't know.

Kim Kitsuragi: "Lucky we found it. You should take stock of what remains, just to be sure some has not made it into the hands of the RCM's adversaries. Organized crime and the like. There might have been police secrets in your notes."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes." He nods. "I think the clothes were taken off to get to that armour he wore, then discarded. They must have stripped him of it fast, too, the scavengers -- in a matter of days."
You: Keep the hunch to yourself.
You: Used to what -- dumpster diving?
Interfacing: No, searching for evidence in the trash.
Inland Empire: Just a feeling. A warning from some part of you.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Or it may just be a coincidence. Either way, something to keep in mind. What else do you see?"
Trash Container: Wow, an Armistice calibre 50 nock cannon, half wrapped in paper tissues! So shiny...

Perception (Smell): Are these the victim's clothes? The smell is not nearly as bad as the cadaver. These clothes could not have been in contact with the deceased for more than two days after his death.
Trash Container: A drab long-sleeved shirt, olive-coloured, appears from the food waste, dripping with pus.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Not really. All we know is -- the victim's clothes are in the trash, the lid was locked, and this establishment had the key. It's just a *small* loose thread."
Interfacing: Not just any man's. This dense cursive -- it's *yours*.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Looks like we found your paperwork."
Cuno: "You askin' me now? It's some shit, copper. How should I know?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes." He nods. "...if we're still assuming the clothes were taken off to get to the armour. They must have stripped him of it fast, the scavengers. In a matter of days."
Composure: Easier said than done -- how could this pathetic cabbage of copy paper and plastic ever become *trs disco*?"
You: Alright then. Seems like a good idea. Right after the garbage, of course. (Accept.)

Kim Kitsuragi: "It would also not hurt to start taking notes on the case." He peers into the trash, where soggy cartons and rags stink, uninvitingly. "Now, tell me what your eagle eyes see. Or are we finished?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Oh." He pauses. "It *might* also be evidence. The mob could have disposed of something in there. We should get it open."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Trash? Food waste from the cafeteria? They lock these containers to keep the derelicts from flocking in. Could be evidence too."
Interfacing: You've done this before. The movements are recorded in your elbows, the methodology in your fingers... you're used to this.
Kim Kitsuragi: "We could try using a prybar -- there's one in my motor carriage. Or..."
Trash Container: You betcha. You know -- this awfully *colonial* mug reminds you of another one, doesn't it? Anyway...
Inland Empire: Nothing. It's nothing. Nothing more to see here.
Trash Container: That's too bad, because none of those things are actually in there. There's just food waste and crisp wrappings.
Jump to: [Kim Kitsuragi: ""Alright. We should go to Garte aga..."]

Kim Kitsuragi: "Officer, this is an official piece of paperwork. It probably contains notes on *numerous* ongoing investigations -- and could even list undercover operatives. Informants. I suggest integrating it into your *style*. For all our sakes."
You: I don't know, it seems foreboding to me somehow. Like there's something in there that's out to get me.
Empathy: His eyes express a rare condolence. Then he picks it up:
You: "There is no Remote Viewers Division, is there?"
You: "Wow! Could we get them here?"
Physical Instrument: *Forget* about it? Like you forgot about your life? No! You cannot forget your own body, and your body cannot forget...
Trash Container: The trash container has *somehow* been unlocked. It's all for you, Harry. The smell of rotten food rises up as you climb inside. This is where you belong...
Trash Container: CheckEquipped("prybar") == true or CheckEquipped("kvalsund_multitool") == true
Physical Instrument: You force open the sealed metal lid with your goddamn *bare hands*. It is open now. It could not resist your supra-human strength.
Trash Container: CheckEquipped("prybar") == false and CheckEquipped("kvalsund_multitool") == false
You: "That's it, I can't pry it open."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Cadaverine odour is faint." The lieutenant smells them. "If these belonged to the deceased, they were removed when he was still in the early stages of decay."
"The victim's clothes?" The lieutenant smells them. "Cadaverine odour is faint. If these belonged to the deceased, they were removed when he was still in the early stages of decay."
Kim Kitsuragi: Darkness engulfs you. The stink of rot nearly knocks you out. For a minute you can smell cigarette smoke wafting in from outside.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Or we could ask for a key from the manager of the Whirling-in-Rags. He probably has one."
Interfacing: Good practice for dumpster diving.
Physical Instrument: No matter how strong you think you are, this is really not something you should be attempting to do with your bare hands.
You: Hang from the prybar with all your weight.
You: "The FUCK kind of metal is this, this is fucking SHIT!"
Cuno: "We should find his gun and kill someone with it."

Kim Kitsuragi: "*Guitar* mark blue jeans. Pockets empty." The lieutenant quickly searches the jeans. "Or *emptied*? He wore them with a belt, too, a wide belt -- the loops appear stretched, but..." He looks into the container.

Kim Kitsuragi: "Boring? Try *dangerous*. You should do a thorough inventory of that -- be sure some has not fallen into the hands of the RCM's enemies: organized crime, or worse... Official notes sometimes contain informants' names, even undercover operatives."
Tutorial Agent: You've acquired an interactable item. Investigate this item further by going to the INTERACT tab in your INVENTORY.
You: "What is the Remote Viewers Division?"
Trash Container: The smell of rotten food rises up at you as you climb inside the trash container.
You: I should... start taking proper notes on the case?
You: "I was trying to open the trash."
Trash Container: You see: milk, an egg-rest with one broken egg in it, some pasta wrapper... Picking up the soggy packages somehow feels familiar.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Well..." He doesn't know what to say.
Conceptualization: What are you talking about? No one's out to get you -- get real man! Upgrade that cop-ledger!
Conceptualization: Challenge accepted. You should be on the lookout for stylistic elements that elevate this cabbage to heights unforeseeable.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Good night, detective," he says, with more gentleness than you've heard from him before.
Kim Kitsuragi: "I agree. We should get someone from the Remote Viewers Division here."
Rhetoric: He's being sarcastic. Do *not* ask what the Remote Viewers Division is.
Kim Kitsuragi: "No-no. We need to investigate now." Just like that, he opens the lid.
Esprit de Corps: The morning will never come.
Jump to: [Trash Container: "The garbage stinks in front of you,..."]

Kim Kitsuragi: "There's a *lot* of it too." He nods approvingly. "*And* you've got an autopsy form in there -- in the back. That light pink copy paper." A miserable looking slip of paper sticks to the board.
Kim Kitsuragi: A few words also come through the metal: "Good night, detective." But they dissipate around you like the smoke; you hear the lieutenant's footfall carry him away.
Trash Container: There's a creaking sound as the prybar slips under the lid. You hang from it, like a moron, huffing and puffing. Clearly the technique is wrong -- but nothing else comes to mind.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Let's ask the manager for the key, this is clearly not working."
Inland Empire: There is. But you won't *like* it. Sweat forms on your brow, your hand is still on the lid...
You: "A thrown out towel, a mug. That's all."
Authority: Hey, maybe it's your paperwork, officer?
Trash Container: Not much to see here anymore. Just a burnt apron and some kitchen towels.
You: "Lieutenant, what do you think could be in there?"
You: "There is no need for sarcasm. I just feel strongly about it, that's all. Maybe it's not connected to the case, but still."
Physical Instrument: Really? Your muscles are down with either one.
